 Photo taken on Nov. 20, 2021 shows the scenery at Wadi Degla natural protectorate in Cairo, Egypt. Wadi Degla is one of the important valleys that are located in the capital Cairo. The valley extends from east to west with a length of 30 km and it passes through the limestone rocks that had remained in the marine environment during the Eocene Epoch in the eastern desert (60 million years). (Xinhua/Sui Xiankai)   Photo taken on Nov. 20, 2021 shows the scenery at Wadi Degla natural protectorate in Cairo, Egypt. Wadi Degla is one of the important valleys that are located in the capital Cairo. The valley extends from east to west with a length of 30 km and it passes through the limestone rocks that had remained in the marine environment during the Eocene Epoch in the eastern desert (60 million years). (Xinhua/Sui Xiankai)  Photo taken on Nov. 20, 2021 shows the scenery at Wadi Degla natural protectorate in Cairo, Egypt. Wadi Degla is one of the important valleys that are located in the capital Cairo. The valley extends from east to west with a length of 30 km and it passes through the limestone rocks that had remained in the marine environment during the Eocene Epoch in the eastern desert (60 million years). (Xinhua/Sui Xiankai)  Photo taken on Nov. 20, 2021 shows the scenery at Wadi Degla natural protectorate in Cairo, Egypt. Wadi Degla is one of the important valleys that are located in the capital Cairo. The valley extends from east to west with a length of 30 km and it passes through the limestone rocks that had remained in the marine environment during the Eocene Epoch in the eastern desert (60 million years). (Xinhua/Sui Xiankai)